==English==
===Etymology===
Via Middle English from Old French, compare French ''[[presse]]''
====Noun====
'''press'''  (''plural:'' '''[[presses]]''')
# A device used to apply pressure to an item.
#:''...a flower '''press'''.''
# A collective term for the [[print]] based [[media]] (both the people and the [[newspaper]]s)
#:''This article appeared in the ''press'''.''
#:''...according to a member of the '''press'''...''
# An enclosed storage space (eg [[closet]], [[cupboard]]).
#:''Put the cups in the '''press'''.''
# General term for a printing machine.
#:''Stop the '''presses'''!''

====Translations====
*French: [[appuyer]]
*German: (1, 2) Presse {{f}}; (4) Drucker {{m}}

===Etymology===
Via Middle English from Old French, compare French ''[[presser]]''
====Verb====
{{en-verb|press|es}}

# To apply [[pressure]] to an item.
#:"'''Press''' any key"
# ''(with "gone"):'' To indicate that a story is being printed.
#:"That story has gone to '''press'''."

====Synonyms====
*[[closet]], [[cupboard]], [[wardrobe]] (''British'')
*a [[printing press]]

